OL,3,CDeputy-elect Le Brun tops the polls
OL,4,Cwith 953 votes
OL,6,F4,759 people came out to cast their
OL,7,Fvote today in Guernsey's By-election
OL,8,Fand it was Ross Le Brun who came out
OL,9,Fon top.
OL,11,FDeputy elect Le Brun got 953 votes and
OL,12,Fwill officially become a politician
OL,13,Fwhen he is sworn in at a later date.
OL,15,FHe fills the space left by former
OL,16,FDeputy Jonathan Le Tocq who was jailed
OL,17,Fafter pleading guilty to 15 sexual
OL,18,Foffences, including possessing
OL,19,Fthousands of indecent images.
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G1/7
