FL,383,380,120,260,000,100
PN,38207
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F382A1777558269
OL,3,CDeputy-elect Le Brun tops the polls
OL,4,Cwith 953 votes
OL,6,F4,749 people came out to vote which is
OL,7,Fa voter turnout of 17.32%. This
OL,8,Fcompares to 19,868 people in 2025
OL,9,Fwhich was a 72% voter turnout.
OL,11,FRegistrar General of Electors Colette
OL,12,FFalla said:
OL,14,F"The turn out was lower than we
OL,15,Fexpected compared to other by-
OL,16,Felections, however it is the first
OL,17,Ftime we've done an island wide
OL,18,Felection so it was a bit of a step
OL,19,Finto the unknown."
OL,1,W~+$z5~{4~k4~k4~sj5  hws         G7/7
